4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, the Alabama Department of
6 Mental Health (ADMH) is authorized to establish
7 standards for its facilities and providers, and
8 pursuant to that authority, has established the ADMH
9 Division of Development Disabilities Community Incident
10 Prevention and Management System (IPMS), which sets
11 requirements for service providers certified by ADMH to
12 protect individuals receiving services for
13 developmental and intellectual disabilities.
14 This bill would establish critical incident type
15 classifications and provider reporting requirements for
16 certain incident types for use in the Division of
17 Developmental Disabilities Community Incident
18 Prevention and Management System.
19 This bill would require ADMH to adopt and amend
20 rules and policies as necessary for implementation.
21 This bill would also prohibit ADMH from
22 requiring or adopting more stringent incident reporting
23 requirements than the requirements provided for by this
24 act or by federal law or regulations.
